SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 696
By Jackson
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend the members of the 168th
Military Police Battalion, Tennessee Army
National Guard, for meritorious service in
support of the Joint Task Force-Southern Border
mission.
WHEREAS, our nation was founded by individuals willing to place service above self in
defense of liberty and the rule of law, and the Volunteer State has long taken pride in the men
and women who answer that call through faithful military service; and
WHEREAS, thousands of Tennesseans continue this proud tradition through service in
the Tennessee Army National Guard, providing critical support to state and federal missions at
home and abroad; and
WHEREAS, the members of the 168th Military Police Battalion, Tennessee Army National
Guard, served with distinction, discipline, and professionalism in support of the Joint Task
Force-Southern Border mission, a complex and demanding operation conducted over thirteen
months in defense of national sovereignty and public safety; and
WHEREAS, under the command of its battalion leadership of Lieutenant Colonel Robert
E. Crowley, the 168th Military Police Battalion, headquartered in Dyersburg, Tennessee,
assumed command of six companies of approximately 650 soldiers to support operations along
a 300-mile operational front extending from Laredo, Texas to Brownsville, Texas; and
WHEREAS, throughout the mission, the Battalion executed continuous, multi-domain
security operations resulting in over 14,000 detections, turn-backs, and assisted apprehensions
in coordination with federal, state, and local law enforcement partners; and
WHEREAS, the Battalion conducted more than thirty counter-unmanned aerial system
engagements and mitigations across the Rio Grande Valley, enhancing air domain awareness
and denying adversary reconnaissance and trafficking operations; and
SJR0696
012734
- 1 -

WHEREAS, the 168th Military Police Battalion successfully planned and executed four
division-approved named operations targeting cartel-controlled hot spots, each operating
continuously, significantly disrupting transnational criminal activity; and
WHEREAS, the Battalion conducted ten coordinated engagements with Mexican military
forces, strengthening cross-border communication, de-escalation, and operational
synchronization; and
WHEREAS, the Battalion supported riverine operations that emplaced 110 buoys in
support of National Defense Areas along the Rio Grande River and adjacent islands,
contributing directly to improved terrain denial and force protection; and
WHEREAS, the members of the Battalion operated as part of an integrated, multi-
agency task force alongside the U.S. Border Patrol, the United States Coast Guard, the Texas
National Guard, Mexican military forces, and local law enforcement agencies, demonstrating
exceptional interoperability and professionalism; and
WHEREAS, the 168th Military Police Battalion established and maintained thirty-one
active manned border sites, supported a total of sixty-six dynamic operational sites, operated
five active camera rooms, and conducted routine dismounted patrols, providing persistent
surveillance and physical presence across the area of operations; and
WHEREAS, through these efforts, the Battalion consistently distinguished itself as a
disciplined, adaptable, and mission-focused organization, often relied upon to establish
operational standards and best practices across the Joint Task Force area of responsibility; and
WHEREAS, having honorably completed this demanding mission, the members of the
168th Military Police Battalion returned home having upheld the highest traditions of the
Tennessee Army National Guard and the United States Army; and
WHEREAS, the service of these soldiers reflects great credit upon themselves, their
families, the Tennessee Army National Guard, and the State of Tennessee; now, therefore,
- 2 - 012734

BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we hereby honor and commend the members of the
168th Military Police Battalion, Tennessee Army National Guard, for their meritorious service in
support of the Joint Task Force-Southern Border mission, and we express our profound
appreciation for their dedication, professionalism, and exemplary service to the State of
Tennessee and the Nation.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
